<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./GregSweetman">GregSweetman</a>: It would be lovely to see a wider variety of potions properly affecting monsters when used against them. <p>
For example, both booze, confusion, blindness and hallucination have the same effect on the monsters.  This is quite understandable given the nature of the effect, but something like "Lose Memories" does nothing to the monsters (perhaps it could un-level them?) 
</p>
<p>
Actually, if that were to be done completely, then all of the stats would need to be recorded for every monster, so that potions of lower x (con/str/dex/wis/int/chr) could affect the monster properly. 
</p>
